 "bull": {
  "claim": "Akamai at 16.9x forward earnings with a B- Valuation grade and a +32.1% mean analyst target is the cheapest name in either live book - the security/compute mix shift keeps grinding (nine straight positive revenue quarters) while the price still discounts a melting CDN.",
  "pillars": [
   "The valuation floor is real: 16.9x forward, 4.1x sales, 20.3x EV/EBITDA with a 58.3% gross margin - the only B-range Valuation grade in the Aristeia book, and the fair-value verdict is Fairly Valued (+18.8%), not stretched.",
   "The revenue base does not shrink: +2.5% to +7.8% YoY for nine consecutive quarters - the security/compute segments are outgrowing the CDN decay every single quarter, and the mix improves mechanically with time.",
   "The street sees the gap: mean target +32.1% above spot across 23 analysts - the largest stated upside in either live book - with EPS revisions already grading B."
  ],
  "catalysts": [
   "Next 2 quarters: revenue growth breaking above 8% YoY as security/compute mix crosses the tipping point.",
   "H2 2026: margin investment cycle ending - EPS turning positive YoY re-rates the 40.7x trailing toward the 16.9x forward.",
   "Ongoing: 4.1x sales limits the downside while the mix story plays out - asymmetric payoff shape."
  ],
  "falsifiers": [
   "Revenue growth falls below +2% YoY for two consecutive quarters - the mix shift is losing to CDN decay.",
   "Net margin breaks below 7% - the investment phase is structural cost, not cycle.",
   "The +32.1% target gap closes by target CUTS rather than price appreciation."
  ]
 },
 "bear": {
  "claim": "Nine straight quarters of 2.5-7.8% revenue growth with EPS DOWN year-over-year in six of them is a no-leverage business, and the 16.9x forward multiple assumes exactly the EPS rebound consensus keeps not getting - while the model ranks it 140 of 201 with C- Growth.",
  "pillars": [
   "The leverage failure is chronic: latest quarter +5.8% revenue with EPS -13.7%; net margin has ground from 17.8% (2024-03) to 9.9% (2026-03) - growth is being bought with margin, quarter after quarter.",
   "The forward multiple is a rolling promise: 40.7x trailing vs 16.9x forward requires EPS to more than double; the dossier's six negative EPS-growth quarters in nine say the denominator keeps not arriving.",
   "Conviction is the weakest in the book: 2.12 recommendation score (vs 1.33-1.44 for INSW/MRVL) - the +32.1% target is wide but weakly held; the model agrees at rank 140 of 201, below the sector median composite (6.57 vs 6.87).",
   "The tape has already paid for stabilization: +57% in twelve months and 18.1% above the 200-day for a business growing 5.8% - the re-rating happened without the earnings inflection."
  ],
  "catalysts": [
   "Next quarter: another negative EPS print - the seventh in ten - resets the 'forward' earnings base lower again.",
   "Next 1-2 quarters: security/compute growth deceleration disclosure inside the flat topline.",
   "H2 2026: hyperscaler edge/CDN pricing pressure compressing the 58.3% gross margin."
